{if:{arg:0}|=|help|# NFX3
this is a bunch of effects with rather messy code compiled into one notsobot tag, just like my first NTFX+ and NitroFXV2. V2 kinda flopped tho
# PRECAUTIONS
- vocoder effects are NOT PRESENT in the bot!
- if you see a "geq" code with waves, ALWAYS use ".resize 640" before executing NFX3!

# HOW DO I REQUEST AN EFFECT?
send it on the "Issues" tab of the repo, https://github.com/nitrogenedits/NFX3, if you have GitHub.

# WHAT DOES THE BOT USE?
FFmpeg and that's it. yup, purely FFmpeg. this is so you can have a **CLEAN** IHTX without the audio clipping as much as in iscript.

# WHAT SUBFUNCTIONS ARE THERE?
- raw: to show the code of an effect
- help: shows this readme
- source: sends the link to the source code repository (this one)

# CAN I FORK THIS REPO?
um sure why not (just release your source code and you'll be fine)}
{if:{arg:0}|=|testcode|then:{set:code|-vf hue=h=180}}
{if:{arg:0}|!=|help|then:{sh:
load {av}
vidlen=$(ffprobe -i $FILE_1 -show_entries format=duration -v quiet -of csv="p=0")
d=$vidlen
sr=$(ffprobe -v error -select_streams a:0 -show_entries stream=sample_rate -of default=nokey=1:noprint_wrappers=1 "$FILE_1" | tr -d '\n')
w=$(ffprobe -v error -select_streams v:0 -show_entries stream=width -of default=nw=1:nk=1 $FILE_1)
h=$(ffprobe -v error -select_streams v:0 -show_entries stream=height -of default=nw=1:nk=1 $FILE_1)
ffmpeg -i $FILE_1 {get:code} -pix_fmt yuv420p ./output/nfx3.mp4}}
}}}
